HEADWORD: groundswell
<hw>ground"swell`</hw> <pr>(ground"sw⟦ecr⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A long, deep wave in the sea, sometimes caused by
distant winds or storms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rising sentiment of support or enthusiasm,
especially among the general public; <as>as, a <ex>groundswell</ex> of
opinion favoring campaign finance reform</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Groundwork</ent>⟦br⟧
